"'''The Prize Pelt: The Tale of Bossk'''" is a short story written by [[Kathy Tyers]] and featured in ''[[Tales of the Bounty Hunters]]'', which was published in December 1996 by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It concerns the backstory of the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]].

==Plot summary==
[[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]] answers [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] call to capture the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] in the hope of skinning [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], his hated [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] foe. To that end, he reluctantly teams with the Wookiee hunter [[Chenlambec]] and his [[Human/Legends|Human]] apprentice, [[Tinian I'att Azur-Jamin|Tinian I'att]], who promise to use their Wookiee contacts to find their prey. According to Chen and Tinian, Chewbacca has taken refuge with escaped Wookiee [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]] on [[Lomabu III]]. Bossk flies his temporary allies to Lomabu III aboard his [[Starship/Legends|ship]], [[Hound's Tooth/Legends|''Hound's Tooth'']], all the while plotting a betrayal. The bloodthirsty Bossk sees this as an opportunity to destroy the entire Wookiee colony. Unbeknownst to him, Chen and Tinian actually plan to betray Bossk – their [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Computer probe/Legends|computer probe]] named [[Flirt]] helps them commandeer the starship.  They redirect Bossk's destructive efforts into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Weapon/Legends|weapons]] towers overlooking a [[Lomabu III penal colony|Wookiee slave camp]], thus freeing the captives. Bossk is trapped aboard his own vessel, and Chen and Tinian hand him over to Imperial [[Governor/Legends|governor]] [[Io Desnand]]. The governor plans to [[Death/Legends|kill]] and skin the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] to make a [[Clothing/Legends|gown]] for his [[Gender/Legends|female]] companion.

